Dwight Mission","primary_persons":[],"hooker_connected_people":["H01138","H00914","H01354","HD2376","HD2818","H01418","I01195","H02770","I01197","I01218","I01220","H01355","H00527"],"person_ids":["X00724","X01977","X02115","X02121","X02122","X02862"],"related_institutions":[],"related_landmarks":[],"tags":["missions","native_american_contact","congregationalist"],"sources":[],"notes":"Founded 1810 at Andover Seminary, Massachusetts by prominent Congregationalists. First American foreign missionary society; first missions to China and Ceylon. Yale President Rev. Timothy Dwight IV (H00914) was among the founding figures; Dwight Mission (established 1820 in present-day Arkansas/Oklahoma for the Cherokee) was named in his honor. The board operated Brainerd Mission (Chattanooga TN, est.1817) where Harriet Ellsworth Blunt (X02121) and Ainsworth Blunt (X02122) served the Cherokee. HOOKER TREE CONNECTIONS: 1. Rev. Timothy Dwight IV (H00914) — Yale President 1795-1817; founding ABCFM figure; Dwight Mission named for him. 5th-generation Hooker descendant. 2. Elias Cornelius (X00724) — ABCFM Secretary of Domestic Correspondence 1819-1832; conducted 1817 missionary tour to Creek and Cherokee; m. Mary Ann Hooker (H01355). 3. Rev. Edward William Hooker (H01354) — corporate ABCFM member from 1840. 4. Harriet Ellsworth Blunt (X02121) — served at Brainerd Mission 1821-1837; granddaughter of Rev. Cyprian Strong (H00299). 5. Ainsworth Blunt (X02122) — Brainerd missionary 1822-1837; accompanied Cherokee on Trail of Tears 1838; first mayor of Dalton GA. 6. Dr. Mary Floyd Cushman (HD2818, gen 8) — ABCFM medical missionary in Angola 1922-1953. 7. Samuel Gelston Dwight (HD2376) — ABCFM missionary to Hawaii; children named for ABCFM colleagues Juliette Cooke and Samuel Castle."}},"crossConnections":[{"type":"civic_connection","related_id":"I00899","link_text":"Reverend Andrew Yates","display_label":"Dominis born at Yates's home; Dwight knew him in Honolulu","slug":"andrew-yates-1773"},{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"X02833","link_text":"John Owen Dominis","display_label":"Both lived in Honolulu's missionary elite for decades","slug":"john-dominis-1832"}]}